<DESCRIPTION>SALE AND PURCHASE AGREEMENT - NEW UNITED MOTOR MANUFACTURING, INC.
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Sale and Purchase Agreement - New United Motor Manufacturing, Inc.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 10.1 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>SALE AND PURCHASE AGREEMENT </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:0px;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">THIS SALE AND PURCHASE AGREEMENT
(the &#147;Agreement&#148;) is made as of the 13</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">th</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"> day of
August, 2010 (the &#147;Effective Date&#148;), between <B>TESLA MOTORS, INC.</B>, (&#147;TESLA&#148;), a Delaware corporation, with its principal office located at 3500 Deer Creek Road, Palo Alto, California 94304 and <B>NEW UNITED MOTOR
MANUFACTURING, INC.</B>, a California corporation, with its place of business at 45500 Fremont Blvd., Fremont, California 94538 (&#147;NUMMI&#148;). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>RECITALS: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Whereas, NUMMI intends to sell certain of its assets; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">B.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Whereas, TESLA desires to purchase and accept certain assets that NUMMI owns and used in the production of automobiles (the &#147;Assets&#148;), including without
limitation, the initial capital asset purchase contemplated by TESLA for $13,469,682.43 million (the &#147;Initial Capital Assets&#148;). Initial Capital Assets include, to the extent transferable, all warranties, indemnification rights, service
agreements and licenses associated with the Initial Capital Assets. For avoidance of doubt, Assets and Initial Capital Assets do not include spare parts associated with the building systems described in the Letter Agreement between NUMMI and TESLA
dated May&nbsp;26, 2010 (the &#147;Real Estate Agreement&#148;). </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NOW THEREFORE, based upon the following
recitals, which are incorporated into and made a part of this Agreement and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of such consideration being acknowledged, the parties hereby agree as follows: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>1.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Sale and Purchase of Initial Capital Assets</U></B>. Upon the terms and subject to the conditions provided in this Agreement, NUMMI hereby agrees to convey, sell,
transfer, and deliver all of NUMMI&#146;s right, title and interest in the Initial Capital Assets to TESLA free and clear of any and all security interests, mortgages, pledges, liens, charges, restrictions, reservations, claims, liabilities,
obligations, encumbrances, leases and interests or claims of every other person or entity of every kind and nature whatsoever (collectively, the &#147;Liens&#148;), and TESLA hereby agrees to purchase and accept the Initial Capital Assets.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>2.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Sale Date for Initial Capital Assets</U></B>. NUMMI shall convey and deliver the Initial Capital Assets to TESLA on the closing date of the Real Estate Agreement
(the &#147;Sale Date&#148;). The sale and purchase of the Assets and the Initial Capital Assets shall be subject to the terms and conditions set forth herein. The parties agree that NUMMI will cease from and after the Effective Date any further
marketing activity or negotiations with third parties with respect to the Initial Capital Assets. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>3.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Purchase Price of Initial Capital Assets</U></B><U><B>. </B></U><B></B> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3.1.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Installment Payment for Initial Capital Assets</U>.</B> Conveyance of the Assets shall be by Bill of Sale substantially in the form of Bill of Sale attached
hereto as <B>Exhibit A</B> (&#147;Bill of Sale&#148;). The aggregate purchase price (&#147;Purchase Price&#148;) for the Initial Capital Assets shall be $13,469,682.43, which purchase price shall also be stated in the Bill of Sale attached hereto as
<B>Exhibit B</B> to be delivered by NUMMI to TESLA on the Sale Date. The Purchase Price will be delivered to NUMMI in two (2)&nbsp;installments, each by wire transfer of immediately available funds as follows: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="8%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(a)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">30% non-refundable initial deposit (the &#147;Initial Deposit&#148;) within three (3)&nbsp;days after the Effective Date; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="8%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(b)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">70% (the &#147;Final Payment&#148;) on the Sale Date. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="8%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>3.2</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Backstop Payment: No Real Estate Closing</U></B><B>.</B> If TESLA fails to make the Final Payment for the Initial Capital Assets, which are identified on
<B>Exhibit C</B>, because the closing of the real estate acquisition of the NUMMI manufacturing facility and land in Fremont, California does not occur, TESLA agrees that NUMMI shall have the right to keep the Initial Deposit as a Breakup Fee and no
additional liability shall accrue to either party. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="8%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>3.3</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Backstop Payment: Real Estate Closing Without Initial Capital Asset Sales</U>.</B> If, prior to or on the Sale Date, TESLA decides not to purchase some or all of
the Initial Capital Assets, NUMMI shall use commercially reasonable efforts to sell the Initial Capital Assets to a third-party and to maximize the sale price of such Initial Capital Assets. If the net sale price to a third-party is less than the
purchase price of the Initial Capital Assets, as agreed to herein by the parties, TESLA shall pay NUMMI a fee equal to the difference between the price that NUMMI sold the Initial Capital Assets to the third party and the price at which TESLA agreed
to purchase the Initial Capital Assets from NUMMI. NUMMI will deduct this fee from the Initial Payment prior to seeking additional payment from TESLA. TESLA further agrees that for the period ending March&nbsp;31, 2011, NUMMI, its agents,
representatives, successors and assigns, shall have access to the Facility under terms to be agreed by the parties, and such access shall not be unreasonably withheld, to undertake all commercially reasonable activities related to the marketing,
sale, and subsequent removal of the Asset(s) from the Facility. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>4.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Payment</U>. </B>TESLA&#146;s payment shall be by wire transfer to an account or accounts as designated in writing by NUMMI. NUMMI shall verify wire payment
transfer prior to conveyance and delivery of the Initial Capital Assets. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>5.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Delivery of Transfer Documents</U>. </B>On the Sale Date, NUMMI shall deliver to TESLA an executed Bill of Sale to convey good title, free and clear of all Liens,
and all other documents, instruments, and writings as NUMMI and TESLA may reasonably deem necessary or appropriate for the legal transfer of such Initial Capital Assets to TESLA pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, including without limitation,
all certificates of title or origin (or like documents), and all documents necessary to transfer to TESLA all manufacturers&#146; warranties, indemnification rights, service agreements and licenses associated with the Initial Capital Assets, to the
extent such manufacturers&#146; warranties, service agreements and licenses are transferable (collectively, the &#147;Transfer Documents&#148;). </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>6.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Possession and Title</U>.</B> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">6.1.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Identification of Initial Capital Assets</U></B>. After payment of the Initial Deposit, TESLA, with assistance from NUMMI, will make commercially reasonable
efforts to segregate the Initial Capital Assets from any other goods or assets and clearly mark and identify the Initial Capital Assets as property purchased from NUMMI. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">6.2.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Teardown and Movement of Initial Capital Assets</U></B>. The parties acknowledge that certain Initial Capital Assets will require extensive teardown and movement
within the NUMMI facility (the &#147;Facility&#148;) to satisfy TESLA&#146;s Model S production requirements. Nevertheless, the Assets are sold &#147;<B>as is&#148; &#147;where is&#148;</B>. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="13%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Movement of Initial Capital Assets Requested by TESLA. </B>Prior to moving any Initial Capital Asset(s), TESLA shall pay in full for such specific
Initial Capital Asset(s) to be moved before moving such Initial Capital Asset(s). Upon receipt of payment in full for such specific Initial Capital Asset(s) to be moved, TESLA shall have the right to move such Initial Capital Asset(s) at
TESLA&#146;s expense, including relocation to TESLA&#146;s powertrain facility in Palo Alto, California. Such teardown and movement of a specific Initial Capital Asset(s) shall be permitted provided it does not interfere with NUMMI&#146;s previously
scheduled teardown schedule. TESLA and its agents will use reasonable care in the dismantling and movement of the Initial Capital Asset(s), and as between TESLA and NUMMI, TESLA shall bear all costs associated with any damage to the Initial Capital
Asset(s). If such teardown activity occurs before the Sale Date, TESLA agrees to indemnify, defend and hold NUMMI harmless for any property damage or injury to third parties directly or indirectly caused by TESLA, its agents and/or representatives
in the process of the teardown and movement of the Initial Capital Asset(s). </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="13%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Movement of Initial Capital Assets Requested by NUMMI</B>. If NUMMI desires to move specific Initial Capital Assets prior to the Sale Date, NUMMI
will obtain the prior written consent of TESLA before moving the Initial Capital Asset(s). NUMMI shall be solely responsible for expenses associated with movement of such specific Initial Capital Assets. NUMMI, its agents and or representatives will
use reasonable care in the movement of the Initial Capital Asset(s). NUMMI shall be solely responsible to TESLA for the financial costs of any damage to the Initial Capital Asset(s) arising from a teardown or movement of the Initial Capital Asset(s)
by NUMMI. TESLA must submit evidence of the physical condition of the Initial Capital Asset(s) prior to any asserted damage claim(s), and any such damage claim(s) must be submitted to NUMMI on or before December&nbsp;31, 2010. If the parties
mutually agree that NUMMI has damaged the Initial Capital Asset(s) listed on <B>Exhibit C</B>, NUMMI, in its sole discretion, may either repair the damaged equipment or refund the price of the Initial Capital Asset(s) to TESLA. NUMMI shall not be
required to replace any damaged Initial Capital Asset. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>7.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Transfer of Software</U></B><B>. </B> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>7.1.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Software Enhancements</U></B><B>.</B> NUMMI will transfer to TESLA with the Initial Capital Assets, at no additional cost, all software required to operate the
Initial Capital Assets. The Initial Capital Assets shall not include any NUMMI performance data, improvements, enhancements or modifications developed by NUMMI, Toyota Motor Corporation (&#147;Toyota&#148;), or any Toyota affiliated company. To the
extent that any of the Initial Capital Assets have software that is licensed to NUMMI, is proprietary, or is otherwise non-transferable, TESLA shall be responsible for obtaining such licenses. A list of non-transferable software associated with the
Initial Capital Assets is on <B>Exhibit E</B>. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>7</B>.<B>2.</B></FONT></TD>

agreement. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Representations and Warranties</U></B><B>.</B> NUMMI represents and warrants to TESLA: (i)&nbsp;NUMMI is a corporation duly incorporated, validly existing and in
good standing under the laws of the State of California, and is authorized to transact business in the State of California, (ii)&nbsp;NUMMI has, and at all times has had, full corporate power and authority to own and lease its properties as such
properties are now owned and leased and to conduct its business as and where such businesses have and are now being conducted, (iii)&nbsp;NUMMI is the lawful and sole (100%)&nbsp;owner of the Initial Capital Assets, and has full right, power and
authority to execute this Agreement and to sell, grant, convey, assign, transfer and deliver and set over unto TESLA all of the Initial Capital Assets, (iv)&nbsp;this Agreement has been duly executed and delivered by NUMMI, and constitutes the
legal, valid, and binding obligation of NUMMI, enforceable in accordance with its terms, (v)&nbsp;the Initial Capital Assets have been checked by NUMMI for hazardous materials and if applicable, MSDS sheets have been prepared, for all petroleum
products or other commercial cleaning, lubrication or similar products used in the ordinary course of business in compliance with environmental laws, (vi)&nbsp;at the Sale Date, NUMMI has no debts, obligations or liabilities, relating to the Initial
Capital Assets, other than obligations for property taxes related to the Initial Capital Assets, which are not yet due and payable (but will be paid by NUMMI when due and payable), (vii)&nbsp;NUMMI has fee simple, good and marketable title to all
right, title, and interest in the Initial Capital Assets, free and clear of all Liens, (viii)&nbsp;no litigation has been filed that would prohibit the transactions contemplated herein or would have a material adverse affect upon any of the Initial
Capital Assets, (ix)&nbsp;NUMMI is in compliance with all of its contractual and legal obligations relating to the Initial Capital Assets, (x)&nbsp;NUMMI is free to deal with TESLA to sell the Initial Capital Assets, and NUMMI&#146;s negotiation and
execution of this Agreement with TESLA do not violate its articles of incorporation or bylaws or any agreement or understanding of NUMMI, (xi)&nbsp;all taxes, including without limitation all property taxes, due and payable with respect to the
Initial Capital Assets have been paid, (xii)&nbsp;NUMMI has not dealt with or engaged any broker or finder in connection with the transactions contemplated by this Agreement; and (xiii)&nbsp;the Initial Capital Assets were in good working condition
as of April&nbsp;1, 2010 when NUMMI ceased production, and NUMMI will provide any existing maintenance records related to the Initial Capital Assets. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

casualty or condemnation, then TESLA may elect (i)&nbsp;not to purchase such damaged Initial Capital Assets and the Purchase Price reduced accordingly, or (ii)&nbsp;to proceed with the purchase of the damaged Initial Capital Assets and all insurance

HARMLESS FROM ANY AND ALL CLAIMS, LAWSUITS, LIABILITIES, DAMAGES, COSTS, EXPENSES OR LOSSES, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION, EXPENSES OF LITIGATION AND REASONABLE ATTORNEYS FEES (COLLECTIVELY, &#147;CLAIMS&#148;), ARISING FROM (I)&nbsp;THE OWNERSHIP
AND OPERATION OF THE INITIAL CAPITAL ASSETS BY NUMMI ON OR PRIOR TO FINAL PAYMENT, INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, CLAIMS ARISING OUT OF THE WILLFUL NEGLECT OF NUMMI OR ITS EMPLOYEES OR AGENTS, (II) ANY BREACH OF ANY REPRESENTATION OR WARRANTY MADE
BY NUMMI IN THIS AGREEMENT, AND (III)&nbsp;ANY BREACH OF ANY COVENANT OR OBLIGATION OF NUMMI IN THIS AGREEMENT. TESLA SHALL GIVE REASONABLE NOTICE TO NUMMI OF ANY SUCH CLAIMS (BUT FAILURE TO GIVE SUCH NOTICE SHALL NOT RELIEVE NUMMI OF ITS OBLIGATION
TO INDEMNIFY). THE INDEMNIFICATION PROVIDED TO TESLA IN THIS SECTION&nbsp;16 SHALL NOT BE THE EXCLUSIVE REMEDY AVAILABLE TO TESLA. TESLA SHALL HAVE ALL OTHER REMEDIES AVAILABLE AT LAW OR EQUITY. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Miscellaneous Provisions</U></B>. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.1. <B><U>No Third Party Beneficiaries</U></B>. This Agreement shall not confer any rights, remedies or obligations upon any person other than the parties and their respective successors and permitted
assigns. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.2. <B><U>Entire
Agreement</U></B>. This Agreement (including the documents referred to herein) constitutes the entire agreement among the parties and supersedes any prior understandings, agreements, or representations by or among the parties, written or oral, with
respect to the subject matter hereof all of which are merged herein. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.3. <B><U>Succession and Assignment</U></B>. This
Agreement shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the parties named herein and their respective successors and permitted assigns. No party may assign either this Agreement or any of its rights, interest, or obligations hereunder without
the prior written approval of the other parties. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.4. <B><U>Counterparts</U></B>. This Agreement may be executed in two or
more counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original but all of which together shall constitute one and the same instrument. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.5. <B><U>Headings</U></B>. The section headings contained in this Agreement are inserted for convenience only and shall not affect in any way the meaning or interpretation of this Agreement.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.6. <B><U>Notices</U>.</B> All notices, requests, demands, claims, and other communications hereunder shall be in writing.
Any notice, request, demand, claim, or other communication hereunder shall be deemed duly delivered five (5)&nbsp;business days after it is sent by registered or certified mail, return receipt requested, postage prepaid, or one business day after it
is sent via a reputable nationwide overnight courier service (such as Federal Express, Airborne Express or DHL), in each case to the intended recipient as set forth below: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>To TESLA</U>: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">TESLA MOTORS, INC. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3500 Deer Creek Road </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Palo Alto, California 94304 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Attention: Deepak Ahuja, Chief Financial Officer </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>To

actually is received by the party for whom it is intended. Any party may change the address to which notices, requests, demands, claims, and other communications hereunder are to be delivered by giving the other parties notice in the manner herein

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.7. <B><U>Governing Law</U></B>. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in
accordance with the internal laws (and not the law of conflicts of laws) of the State of California. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.8. <B><U>Amendments
and Waivers</U></B>. The parties may mutually amend any provision of this Agreement at any time. No amendment of any provision of this Agreement shall be valid unless the same shall be in writing and signed by both parties. No waiver by any Party of
any default, misrepresentation, or breach of warranty or covenant hereunder, whether intentional or not, shall be deemed to extend to any prior or subsequent default, misrepresentation, or breach of warranty or covenant hereunder or affect in any
way any rights arising by virtue of any prior or subsequent such occurrence. All waivers shall be in writing. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.9.
<B><U>Severability</U></B>. Any term or provision of this Agreement that is invalid or unenforceable in any situation in any jurisdiction shall not affect the validity or enforceability of the remaining terms and provisions hereof or the validity or
enforceability of the offending term or provision in any other situation or in any other jurisdiction. If the final judgment of a court of competent jurisdiction declares that any term or provision hereof is invalid or unenforceable, the parties
agree that the court making the determination of invalidity or unenforceability shall have the power to reduce the scope, duration, or area of the term or provision, to delete specific words or phrases, or to replace any invalid or unenforceable
term or provision with a term or provision that is valid and enforceable and that comes closest to expressing the intention of the invalid or unenforceable term or provision, and this Agreement shall be enforceable as so modified after the
expiration of the time within which such a judgment may be modified or appealed. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.10. <B><U>Expenses</U></B>. Except as
otherwise expressly provided for in this Agreement, each of the parties shall bear its own costs and expenses (including attorneys, accountants, and appraisers&#146; fees) incurred in connection with the preparation, execution and performance of
this Agreement and the transactions contemplated hereby. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.11. <B><U>Construction</U></B>. TESLA and NUMMI have participated
jointly in the negotiation and drafting of this Agreement. The language used in this Agreement shall be deemed to be the language chosen jointly by the parties hereto to express their mutual intent, and no rule of strict construction shall be
applied against any party. Any reference to any federal, state, local, or foreign statute or law shall be deemed also to refer to all rules and regulations promulgated thereunder, unless the context requires otherwise. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">20.12. <B><U>Time of Essence.</U></B> Time shall be of the essence in the performance of the obligations set forth in this Agreement.

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>EXHIBIT A </U></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>FORM OF BILL OF SALE </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">KNOW ALL MEN BY THESE PRESENTS that NEW UNITED MOTOR MANUFACTURING, INC. (&#147;NUMMI&#148;), a California corporation, having its principal place of business at 45500 Fremont Blvd., Fremont, California
94538 for and in consideration of the sum of exactly US$<U>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</U> (the &#147;Purchase Price&#148;), paid by TESLA MOTORS, INC. (&#147;TESLA&#148;), a Delaware corporation, receipt of which is
acknowledged, has bargained, sold, granted, and conveyed and, by these presents, does hereby unconditionally and irrevocably bargain, sell, grant, and convey unto TESLA and TESLA&#146;s successors and assigns, those certain initial capital assets
described on &#147;Attachment A&#148; which is attached hereto and incorporated by reference herein (the &#147;Initial Capital Assets&#148;), together with all original certificates of title or origin (or like documents), and all manufacturers&#146;
warranties, service agreements and licenses associated with such Initial Capital Assets, all free and clear of any and all security interests, mortgages, pledges, liens, charges, restrictions, reservations, claims, liabilities, obligations,
encumbrances, leases and interests or claims of every other person of every kind and nature whatsoever. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">TO HAVE AND TO HOLD
the same unto TESLA and TESLA&#146;S successors and assigns forever. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NUMMI represents and warrants to TESLA: (i)&nbsp;NUMMI
has fee simple, good and marketable title to all right, title, and interest in the Initial Capital Assets, free and clear of all security interests, mortgages, pledges, liens, charges, restrictions, reservations, claims, liabilities, obligations,
encumbrances, leases and interests or claims of every other person of every kind and nature whatsoever (each a &#147;Lien&#148;) and can and does deliver such title to the Initial Capital Assets to TESLA free of any Lien, and (ii)&nbsp;NUMMI has
obtained all approvals and consents of all necessary persons who must approve the transfer of the Initial Capital Assets. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY PROVIDED IN THE PREVIOUS PARAGRAPH OF THIS BILL OF SALE AND IN SECTIONS 9 AND 11 OF THAT CERTAIN SALE AND PURCHASE
AGREEMENT DATED AUGUST 13, 2010 BY AND BETWEEN NUMMI AND TESLA (THE &#147;AGREEMENT&#148;), NUMMI MAKES NO REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, ORAL OR WRITTEN, CONCERNING OR WITH RESPECT TO THE INITIAL CAPITAL ASSETS. THE
SALE AND TRANSFER OF THE INITIAL CAPITAL ASSETS FROM NUMMI TO ITS IS MADE ON AN &#147;AS IS&#148;, &#147;WHERE IS&#148;, &#147;ALL FAULTS&#148; BASIS EFFECTIVE AS OF THE SALE DATE. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Bill of Sale shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the internal laws (and not the law of conflicts of laws) of the
State of California. This Bill of Sale shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the parties named herein and their respective successors and assigns. Each party hereto agrees, upon the reasonable request of the other party hereto, to make,
execute and deliver all documents or instruments of any kind or character, and to perform all such other actions, that may be reasonably necessary or proper to effectuate, confirm, perform or carry out the terms and provisions of this Bill of Sale.
</FONT></P>

subject to the Sale and Purchase Agreement dated August&nbsp;13, 2010 by and between NUMMI and TESLA (the &#147;Agreement&#148;), and all terms, conditions, disclosures, exhibits, representations and warranties, covenants, indemnification
obligations, exceptions, and acknowledgements contained therein are incorporated herein by reference and shall not be deemed to be merged herein but shall survive execution and delivery hereof. Capitalized terms used herein and not defined herein
shall have the meanings set forth in the Agreement. No provision of this Bill of Sale shall be deemed to enlarge, alter or amend the terms or provisions of the Agreement. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary set forth herein, if there is any
conflict between the terms and conditions of this Bill of Sale and the terms and conditions of the Agreement, the terms and conditions of the Agreement shall control. All representations, warranties, covenants, and other obligations in this Bill of
Sale, and any other certificate or document delivered pursuant to this Bill of Sale, shall survive the date hereof. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Bill
of Sale may be executed in two or more counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original but all of which together shall constitute the same instrument. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>EXHIBIT B </U></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>BILL OF SALE FOR INITIAL CAPITAL ASSETS </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">KNOW ALL MEN BY THESE PRESENTS that NEW UNITED MOTOR MANUFACTURING, INC. (<B>&#147;NUMMI&#148;</B>), a California corporation, having its principal place of business at 45500 Fremont Blvd., Fremont,
California 94538 for and in consideration of the sum of exactly <B>$13,469,682.43 </B>million (the <B>&#147;Purchase Price&#148;</B>), paid by <B>TESLA MOTORS, INC. (&#147;TESLA&#148;)</B>, a Delaware corporation, receipt of which is acknowledged,
has bargained, sold, granted, and conveyed and, by these presents, does hereby unconditionally and irrevocably bargain, sell, grant, and convey unto TESLA and TESLA&#146;s successors and assigns, those certain initial capital assets described on
Exhibit C, which is attached hereto and incorporated by reference herein (the <B>&#147;Initial Capital Assets&#148;</B>), together with all original certificates of title or origin (or like documents), and all manufacturers&#146; warranties, service
agreements and licenses associated with such Initial Capital Assets, all free and clear of any and all security interests, mortgages, pledges, liens, charges, restrictions, reservations, claims, liabilities, obligations, encumbrances, leases and
interests or claims of every other person of every kind and nature whatsoever. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">TESLA&#146;s payment of the Purchase Price
shall be pursuant to the following terms and conditions: (i)&nbsp;TESLA shall make a initial 30% non-refundable payment within three (3)&nbsp;days of the Effective Date; and (ii)&nbsp;unless the parties otherwise agree alter the payment schedule,
TESLA shall pay the remaining 70% of the Purchase Price to NUMMI on or before the Sale Date. NUMMI shall not permit TESLA to teardown or move a specific Asset identified in <B>Exhibit C</B> until TESLA has made payment in full for the specific
Asset(s). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">TO HAVE AND TO HOLD the same unto TESLA and TESLA&#146;s successors and assigns forever. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NUMMI represents and warrants to TESLA: (i)&nbsp;NUMMI has fee simple, good and marketable title to all right, title, and interest in the
Initial Capital Assets, free and clear of all security interests, mortgages, pledges, liens, charges, restrictions, reservations, claims, liabilities, obligations, encumbrances, leases and interests or claims of every other person of every kind and
nature whatsoever (each a <B>&#147;Lien&#148;</B>) and can and does deliver such title to the Initial Capital Assets to TESLA free of any Lien, and (ii)&nbsp;NUMMI has obtained all approvals and consents of all necessary persons who must approve the
transfer of the Initial Capital Assets. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY PROVIDED IN THE PREVIOUS PARAGRAPH OF THIS BILL OF SALE AND IN
SECTIONS 9 AND 11 OF THAT CERTAIN SALE AND PURCHASE AGREEMENT DATED AUGUST 13, 2010 BY AND BETWEEN NUMMI AND TESLA (THE <B>&#147;AGREEMENT&#148;</B>), NUMMI MAKES NO REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, ORAL OR WRITTEN,
CONCERNING OR WITH RESPECT TO THE INITIAL CAPITAL ASSETS. THE SALE AND TRANSFER OF THE INITIAL CAPITAL ASSETS FROM NUMMI TO TESLA IS MADE ON AN <B>&#147;AS IS&#148;</B>, <B>&#147;WHERE IS&#148;</B>, <B>&#147;ALL FAULTS&#148;</B> BASIS EFFECTIVE AS
OF THE SALE DATE. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Bill of Sale shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the internal laws (and not the law
of conflicts of laws) of the State of California. This Bill of Sale shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the parties named herein and their respective successors and assigns. Each party hereto agrees, upon the reasonable request of the
other party hereto, to make, execute and deliver any and all documents or instruments of any kind or character, and to perform all such other actions, that may be reasonably necessary or proper to effectuate, confirm, perform or carry out the terms
and provisions of this Bill of Sale. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Bill of Sale is
subject to the Sale and Purchase Agreement dated as of August&nbsp;13, 2010 by and between NUMMI and TESLA (the <B>&#147;Agreement&#148;</B>), and all terms, conditions, disclosures, exhibits, representations and warranties, covenants,
indemnification obligations, exceptions, and acknowledgements contained therein are incorporated herein by reference and shall not be deemed to be merged herein but shall survive execution and delivery hereof. Capitalized terms used herein and not
defined herein shall have the meanings set forth in the Agreement. No provision of this Bill of Sale shall be deemed to enlarge, alter or amend the terms or provisions of the Agreement. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary set forth herein, if
there is any conflict between the terms and conditions of this Bill of Sale and the terms and conditions of the Agreement, the terms and conditions of the Agreement shall control. All representations, warranties, covenants, and other obligations in
this Bill of Sale, and any other certificate or document delivered pursuant to this Bill of Sale, shall survive the date hereof. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Bill of Sale may be executed in two or more counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original but all of which together shall constitute one and the same instrument. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have duly executed and delivered this Bill of Sale effective as of the <U>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</U>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>EXHIBIT F </U></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>BILL OF SALE FOR SPARE PARTS FOR INITIAL CAPITAL ASSETS </U></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">KNOW ALL MEN BY THESE PRESENTS that NEW UNITED MOTOR MANUFACTURING, INC. (<B>&#147;NUMMI&#148;</B>), a California corporation, having its
principal place of business at 45500 Fremont Blvd., Fremont, California 94538 for and in consideration of the sum of exactly <B>US$1,700,000 </B>million (the &#147;<B>Purchase Price&#148;</B>), paid by TESLA MOTORS, INC. (<B>&#147;TESLA&#148;</B>),
a Delaware corporation, receipt of which is acknowledged, has bargained, sold, granted, and conveyed and, by these presents, does hereby unconditionally and irrevocably bargain, sell, grant, and convey unto TESLA and TESLA&#146;s successors and
assigns, those certain spare parts for the initial capital assets described on Exhibit F (<B>&#147;Spare Parts&#148;</B>), which is attached hereto and incorporated by reference herein, all free and clear of any and all security interests,
mortgages, pledges, liens, charges, restrictions, reservations, claims, liabilities, obligations, encumbrances, leases and interests or claims of every other person of every kind and nature whatsoever. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">TESLA&#146;s payment of the Purchase Price shall be pursuant to the following terms and conditions: (i)&nbsp;TESLA shall make an initial
30% non-refundable payment of $510,000.00 within three (3)&nbsp;days of the Effective Date; and (ii)&nbsp;unless the parties otherwise agree alter the payment schedule, TESLA shall pay the remaining 70% of the Purchase Price, or $1,190,000.00, to
NUMMI on or before the Sale Date. NUMMI shall not permit TESLA to remove the Spare Parts from the NUMMI facility until TESLA has made payment in full for the specific Spare Part. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">TO HAVE AND TO HOLD the same unto TESLA and TESLA&#146;s successors and assigns forever. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NUMMI represents and warrants to TESLA: NUMMI has fee simple, good and marketable title to all right, title, and interest in the Spare
Parts, free and clear of all security interests, mortgages, pledges, liens, charges, restrictions, reservations, claims, liabilities, obligations, encumbrances, leases and interests or claims of every other person of every kind and nature whatsoever
(each a <B>&#147;Lien&#148;</B>) and can and does deliver such title to the Spare Parts to TESLA free of any Lien, and (ii)&nbsp;NUMMI has obtained all approvals and consents of all necessary persons who must approve the transfer of Spare Parts.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY PROVIDED IN THE PREVIOUS PARAGRAPH OF THIS BILL OF SALE AND IN SECTIONS 9 AND 11 OF THAT CERTAIN SALE AND
PURCHASE AGREEMENT DATED AUGUST 13, 2010 BY AND BETWEEN NUMMI AND TESLA (THE <B>&#147;AGREEMENT&#148;</B>), NUMMI MAKES NO REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, ORAL OR WRITTEN, CONCERNING OR WITH RESPECT TO THE SPARE PARTS.
THE SALE AND TRANSFER OF THE SPARE PARTS FROM NUMMI TO TESLA IS MADE ON AN <B>&#147;AS IS&#148;, &#147;WHERE IS&#148;, &#147;ALL FAULTS&#148;</B> BASIS EFFECTIVE AS OF THE DATE. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Bill of Sale shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the internal laws (and not the law of conflicts of laws) of the
State of California. This Bill of Sale shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the parties named herein and their respective successors and assigns. Each party hereto agrees, upon the reasonable request of the other party hereto, to make,
execute and deliver any and all documents or instruments of any kind or character, and to perform all such other actions, that may be reasonably necessary or proper to effectuate, confirm, perform or carry out the terms and provisions of this Bill
of Sale. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Bill of Sale is
subject to the Sale and Purchase Agreement dated as of August&nbsp;13, 2010 by and between NUMMI and TESLA (the <B>&#147;Agreement&#148;</B>), and all terms, conditions, disclosures, exhibits, representations and warranties, covenants,
indemnification obligations, exceptions, and acknowledgements contained therein are incorporated herein by reference and shall not be deemed to be merged herein but shall survive execution and delivery hereof. Capitalized terms used herein and not
defined herein shall have the meanings set forth in the Agreement. No provision of this Bill of Sale shall be deemed to enlarge, alter or amend the terms or provisions of the Agreement. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary set forth herein, if
there is any conflict between the terms and conditions of this Bill of Sale and the terms and conditions of the Agreement, the terms and conditions of the Agreement shall control. All representations, warranties, covenants, and other obligations in
this Bill of Sale, and any other certificate or document delivered pursuant to this Bill of Sale, shall survive the date hereof. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Bill of Sale may be executed in two or more counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original but all of which together shall constitute one and the same instrument. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have duly executed and delivered this Bill of Sale effective as of the <U>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</U>
day of <U>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</U> , 2010. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P><DIV ALIGN="right">

 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 10.2
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>ADDENDUM NO. 1 </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>to the SALE AND PURCHASE AGREEMENT </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%;padding-bottom:0px;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">THIS
ADDENDUM NO. 1 (&#147;Addendum No.&nbsp;1&#148;) to the SALE AND PURCHASE AGREEMENT (&#147;Agreement&#148;) is made as of the 23</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">rd</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"> day of September, 2010 (the &#147;Addendum Effective Date&#148;), between TESLA and NUMMI. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>RECITALS: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Whereas, the parties entered into the Agreement dated August&nbsp;13, 2010 with respect to Initial Capital Assets; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">B.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NUMMI intends to sell additional assets (&#147;Additional Assets&#148;) to Tesla. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The parties hereby agree as follows: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>1.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Sale and Purchase of Additional Assets</U></B>. Upon the terms and subject to the conditions provided in this Agreement, NUMMI hereby agrees to convey, sell,
transfer, and deliver all of NUMMI&#146;s right, title and interest in the Additional Assets to TESLA free and clear of any Liens (as defined in the Agreement), and TESLA hereby agrees to purchase and accept the Additional Assets. As used in this
Addendum No.&nbsp;1, Additional Assets are as follows: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Phase 2 Capital Assets specified in Exhibit A to this Addendum No.&nbsp;1; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Blanking Line Assets and Spare Parts for Blanking Line Assets specified in Exhibit B to this Addendum No.&nbsp;1; CMM Assets specified in Exhibit C to
this Addendum No.&nbsp;1; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Incidentals specified in Exhibit D to this Addendum No.&nbsp;1. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Sale Date for Additional Assets</U></B>. NUMMI shall convey and deliver the Additional Assets to TESLA on the Sale Date. The sale and purchase of the Additional
Assets shall be subject to the terms and conditions set forth herein. The parties agree that NUMMI will cease from and after the Addendum Effective Date any further marketing activity or negotiations with third parties with respect to the Additional
Assets. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Installment Payment for Additional Assets</U>.</B> Conveyance of the Assets shall be by Bill of Sale substantially in the form of Bill of Sale attached as
<B>Exhibit A</B> to the Agreement. The aggregate purchase price (&#147;Purchase Price&#148;) for the Additional Assets shall be $1,540,735.14, which purchase price shall also be stated in a separate Bill of Sale attached as Exhibit B to the
Agreement to be delivered by NUMMI to TESLA on the Sale Date. The Purchase Price will be delivered to NUMMI in two (2)&nbsp;installments, each by wire transfer of immediately available funds as follows: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">30% non-refundable initial deposit within three (3)&nbsp;days after the Addendum Effective Date; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Applicable Terms.</U></B> This Addendum No.&nbsp;1 shall be incorporated into, and be a part of the Agreement. Unless otherwise specified in this Addendum
No.&nbsp;1, all terms regarding Initial Capital Assets and set forth in the Agreement will apply to Additional Assets. The Exhibit attached to this Addendum No.&nbsp;1 are incorporated herein by reference and made a part hereof. All other terms in
the Agreement will remain in full force and effect, except that NUMMI does not represent that the CMM Assets were in good working condition as of April&nbsp;1, 2010 when NUMMI ceased production. For purposes of the CMM Assets only, NUMMI represents,
and TESLA agrees, that the CMM Assets are in good working condition as of the Addendum Effective Date. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">IN
WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties hereto have executed this Addendum No.&nbsp;1 as of the date first above written. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

terms are as follows: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1. <B><I>Waiver of Termination Right</I></B>. NUMMI hereby waives its right to terminate the Letter
Agreement pursuant to terms set forth in the second sentence of Section&nbsp;2(c)(ii) in the Letter Agreement. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2.
<B><I>Removal of Equipment</I></B>. The last sentence of Section&nbsp;4(b)(iii)(2) of the Letter Agreement is replaced with the following sentence: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:8%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Upon 2 months advance notice which Buyer shall give no later than August&nbsp;1, 2010 that specified equipment owned by Seller will interfere with Buyer&#146;s Model S manufacturing operations, such
equipment will be removed by Seller by March&nbsp;31, 2011, except as the parties may agree otherwise in writing. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3.
<B><I>Access by NUMMI</I></B>. The first four sentences of Section&nbsp;4(b)(v)(1) of the Letter Agreement are replaced with the following three sentences: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 10.6
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>AMENDMENT NO.&nbsp;4 TO LETTER AGREEMENT </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">THIS AMENDMENT NO.&nbsp;4 TO LETTER AGREEMENT (this &#147;Amendment No.&nbsp;4&#148;) is made and entered into as of this 13th day of October, 2010 (the &#147;Effective Date&#148;) by and between New
United Motor Manufacturing, Inc., a California corporation (&#147;Seller&#148;), and Tesla Motors, Inc., a Delaware corporation (&#147;Buyer&#148;). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>RECITALS</U>: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A. Seller and Buyer entered into that certain Letter Agreement
dated May&nbsp;26, 2010, as amended by (i)&nbsp;that certain Amendment No.&nbsp;1 to Letter Agreement dated June&nbsp;15, 2010, and (ii)&nbsp;those certain e-mail amendments extending the Closing Date dated October&nbsp;1, 2010 and October&nbsp;8,
2010 (as amended, the &#147;Letter Agreement&#148;) pursuant to which Seller agreed to sell and Buyer agreed to purchase that certain real property in the County of Alameda, State of California, commonly known as 45500 Fremont Boulevard, Fremont,
California, as more particularly described in the Letter Agreement, on all of the terms and conditions set forth therein. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">B.
Seller and Buyer now desire to enter into this Amendment No.&nbsp;4 to amend the Letter Agreement on the terms and conditions set forth in this Amendment No.&nbsp;4. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the promises, terms and conditions contained herein and such other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged, Seller and
Buyer hereby agree as follows: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A. <U>Defined Terms and Recitals</U>. Except as otherwise defined herein, all capitalized
terms used herein but not otherwise defined herein shall have the meanings set forth in the Letter Agreement. Seller and Buyer hereby agree that the recitals set forth hereinabove are true and correct and incorporated into this Amendment No.&nbsp;4.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">B. <U>Extension of Closing Date</U>. The Closing Date is extended to October&nbsp;15, 2010 or such earlier date as may be
mutually agreed upon by Seller and Buyer in writing. As used in the Agreement, the terms &#147;Closing&#148; and &#147;Closing Date&#148; shall hereafter mean October&nbsp;15, 2010 (or such earlier date). </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">C. <U>No Further Modifications</U>. Except as set forth herein, the Letter Agreement remains unmodified and in full force and effect. In
the event of any inconsistency between the provisions of the Letter Agreement and this Amendment No.&nbsp;4, the terms of this Amendment No.&nbsp;4 shall control. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">D. <U>Governing Law</U>. This Amendment No.&nbsp;4 shall be governed by, construed and enforced in accordance with, the laws of the State of California. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">E. <U>Counterparts</U>. This Amendment No.&nbsp;4 may be executed in two or more counterparts, which when taken together shall constitute
one and the same instrument. The parties contemplate that they may be executing counterparts of the Amendment No.&nbsp;4 transmitted by facsimile and agree </FONT></P>

and intend that a signature by facsimile machine shall bind the party so signing with the same effect as though the signature were an original signature. </FONT></P>

<DESCRIPTION>AMENDMENT NO. 6 TO THE LETTER AGREEMENT - NEW UNITED MOTOR MANUFACTURING, INC.
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Amendment No. 6 to the Letter Agreement - New United Motor Manufacturing, Inc.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">CONFIDENTIAL
TREATMENT REQUESTED BY TESLA MOTORS, INC. </FONT></P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 10.8 </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>AMENDMENT NO.&nbsp;6 TO LETTER AGREEMENT </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">THIS AMENDMENT NO. 6 TO LETTER AGREEMENT (this &#147;Amendment No.&nbsp;6&#148;) is made and entered into as of this 19th day of October, 2010 (the &#147;Effective Date&#148;) by and between New United
Motor Manufacturing, Inc., a California corporation (&#147;Seller&#148;), and Tesla Motors, Inc., a Delaware corporation (&#147;Buyer&#148;). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>RECITALS</U>: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A. Seller and Buyer entered into that certain Letter Agreement
dated May&nbsp;26, 2010 (the &#147;Original Letter Agreement&#148;), as amended by (i)&nbsp;that certain Amendment No.&nbsp;1 to Letter Agreement dated June&nbsp;15, 2010, (ii)&nbsp;those certain e-mail amendments extending the Closing Date dated
October&nbsp;1, 2010 and October&nbsp;8, 2010, (iii)&nbsp;that certain Amendment No.&nbsp;4 to Letter Agreement dated October&nbsp;13, 2010, and (iv)&nbsp;that certain Amendment No.&nbsp;5 to the Letter Agreement dated October&nbsp;15, 2010 (as
amended, the &#147;Letter Agreement&#148;) pursuant to which Seller agreed to sell and Buyer agreed to purchase that certain real property in the County of Alameda, State of California, commonly known as 45500 Fremont Boulevard, Fremont, California,
as more particularly described in the Letter Agreement (&#147;Property&#148;), on all of the terms and conditions set forth therein. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">B. Seller and Buyer now desire to enter into this Amendment No.&nbsp;6 to amend the Letter Agreement on the terms and conditions set forth in this Amendment No.&nbsp;6. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the promises, terms and conditions contained herein and such other good and valuable consideration,
the receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged, Seller and Buyer hereby agree as follows: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A. <U>Defined Terms and
Recitals</U>. Except as otherwise defined herein, all capitalized terms used herein but not otherwise defined herein shall have the meanings set forth in the Letter Agreement. Seller and Buyer hereby agree that the recitals set forth hereinabove are
true and correct and incorporated into this Amendment No.&nbsp;6. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">B. <U>Modifications to Letter Agreement</U>. The parties
agree that from and after the date of this Amendment No.&nbsp;6, the Letter Agreement shall be modified as follows: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1.
<U>Building Systems Spare Parts</U>. The parties hereby acknowledge and agree that certain personal property commonly referred to by the parties as the &#147;Building Systems Spare Parts&#148; (located in that certain area described on
<U>Schedule&nbsp;1</U> attached hereto and made a part hereof) are part of the &#147;Property&#148; as defined in the Original Letter Agreement. At the Closing, Seller shall transfer title to such Building Systems Spare Parts by a bill of sale in
the form attached hereto as <U>Exhibit&nbsp;A</U>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2. <U>Demolition of Model S Area</U>. Seller shall, at its sole cost and
expense, cause the demolition of that certain area commonly referred to by the parties as the &#147;Model S Area&#148; and more particularly described on <U>Schedule 2</U> attached hereto and made a part hereof. Seller shall endeavor to complete
such demolition on or before March&nbsp;31, 2011, subject to any force majeure delays. As used herein, &#147;force majeure delays&#148; shall include any delays </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">- 1 -
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">***</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Confidential treatment requested pursuant to a request for confidential treatment filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Omitted portions have been filed
separately with the Commission. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">CONFIDENTIAL
TREATMENT REQUESTED BY TESLA MOTORS, INC. </FONT></P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
attributable to labor stoppage, interruptions in the supply of utilities, material shortage, the imposition of building moratoria or other laws or governmental requirements that prevent or delay
work, acts of war, terrorism or civil unrest, weather conditions, or acts of God or actions of governmental agencies with jurisdiction over the Property, or any other events, conditions or circumstances outside of the reasonable control of Seller.
The provisions set forth in this paragraph shall survive Closing. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3. <U>Phase 2 Water Service</U>. Buyer hereby acknowledges
receipt of a copy of that certain First Amendment to the Water Service Agreement, dated July&nbsp;22, 2010, by and between Seller and The Alameda County Water District (&#147;ACWD&#148;), pursuant to which Seller elected not to cause the ACWD to
construct &#147;Phase 2&#148; of a twelve inch pipeline to provide water service from the San Francisco Public Utilities Commission water system to the Property (the &#147;Phase 2 Water Service&#148;). </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Notwithstanding anything to the contrary set forth in the Letter Agreement, Buyer hereby acknowledges and agrees that in no event shall
Seller have any obligation to provide the Phase 2 Water Service to the Property, or have any liability in connection with any failure to provide the Phase 2 Water Service to the Property. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">4. <U>Temporary Water Pipeline Easement</U>. At Closing, Seller and Buyer shall enter into a Utility Easement Agreement burdening that
certain parcel adjacent to the Property commonly known as 45500 Fremont Boulevard, Fremont, California (&#147;Parcel 3&#148;) (the &#147;Parcel 3 Utility Easement Agreement&#148;), pursuant to which Seller shall grant to Buyer (a)&nbsp;a temporary
easement over that certain area in which the existing pipeline (which previously provided water service from the San Francisco Public Utilities Commission water system to the Property) is located (the &#147;Existing Pipeline Easement Area&#148;),
and (b)&nbsp;an easement over that certain area along the eastern and northern boundaries of Parcel 3 (as more particularly described in the Parcel 3 Utility Easement Agreement) (the &#147;New Pipeline Easement Area&#148;). Buyer hereby agrees to
promptly and diligently complete the construction of a new pipeline in the New Pipeline Easement Area after Closing. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the easement over the Existing Pipeline Easement Area shall automatically terminate with no further
action required by either party upon the earlier of (c)&nbsp;the completion of the construction of a new pipeline in the New Pipeline Easement Area or (d)&nbsp;December&nbsp;31, 2011, and upon such termination, Buyer shall have no further rights to
use the existing pipelines located in the Existing Pipeline Easement Area. Furthermore, notwithstanding anything to the contrary set forth herein, if Buyer fails to complete the construction of a new pipeline in the New Pipeline Easement Area on or
before December&nbsp;31, 2012, the easement over the New Pipeline Easement Area shall automatically terminate with no further action required by either party. The parties hereby acknowledge and agree that Seller&#146;s sole remedy in the event that
Buyer fails to complete any construction in the time periods set forth herein shall be the automatic termination of the applicable easements. The provisions set forth in this paragraph shall survive Closing. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">5. <U>Phase I Environmental Report</U>. Seller shall cause that certain draft &#147;Phase I&#148; environmental report prepared by Iris
Environmental Consulting to be completed by December&nbsp;31, 2010 to ASTM standards and certified to Buyer and its lender, the United States </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">- 2 -
</FONT></P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">CONFIDENTIAL
